OL,3,CWhy dialling 999 doesn't always mean
OL,4,Cgetting an ambulance - explained
OL,6,FWhen someone dials 999, they are put
OL,7,Fthrough to trained call handlers who
OL,8,Fuse a set of questions to understand
OL,9,Fthe patient's condition: Is the
OL,10,Fpatient breathing? Is the patient
OL,11,Fawake?
OL,13,FLow risk cases - a minor fracture,
OL,14,Fminor burn or back pain for example -
OL,15,Fare transferred to Hear and Treat
OL,16,Fclinicians, nurses and other medical
OL,17,Fprofessionals based in SWASFT's
OL,18,Fcontrol rooms, for more assessment and
OL,19,Fadvice. Depending on the outcome:
