OL,3,CWhy dialling 999 doesn't always mean
OL,4,Cgetting an ambulance - explained
OL,6,FAmbulances are only sent out if
OL,7,Foperators think one is really needed.
OL,8,FThis approach is supposed to ensure
OL,9,Fthat the real emergencies ` cardiac
OL,10,Farrests, severe trauma, breathing
OL,11,Fdifficulties ` get an ambulance in the
OL,12,Ftarget time of seven minutes. This is
OL,13,Falways a challenge in an area of
OL,14,F10,000 square miles - much of it rural.
OL,16,FAmbulance services across England have
OL,17,Ffaced more and more pressure from
OL,18,Frising call volumes, leading to new
OL,19,Fsystems like Hear and Treat to free up
OL,20,Fcrews for when it matters most.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
