OL,3,CWhy dialling 999 doesn't always mean
OL,4,Cgetting an ambulance - explained
OL,6,F"We would always want to encourage
OL,7,Fpatients to phone us when they feel
OL,8,Fthey need an ambulance response, but I
OL,9,Fthink we have a duty of care to ensure
OL,10,Fwe assign the right response to the
OL,11,Fright patients."
OL,13,FBut is the Hear and Treat system safe?
OL,14,FCould seriously ill patients be
OL,15,Fslipping through the net if no one is
OL,16,Factually going out to examine them
OL,17,Fface-to-face? Jon Knight says checks
OL,18,Fand balances are in place.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@PO]
