OL,3,CWhy dialling 999 doesn't always mean
OL,4,Cgetting an ambulance - explained
OL,6,F"Every single one of those calls will
OL,7,Fbe reviewed by a senior experienced
OL,8,Fclinician within the Emergency
OL,9,FOperations Centre - someone with a
OL,10,Fnumber of years of training and
OL,11,Fexperience that allows them to assess
OL,12,Fcalls rapidly. Moreover, the majority
OL,13,Fof what we do is referring patients to
OL,14,Fother pathways and a significant
OL,15,Fproportion of other pathways will have
OL,16,Fa senior clinician at that end of the
OL,17,Fpathway as well, who also assesses the
OL,18,Fcall."
